<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_dyzærdyg" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dyzærdyg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>duzærdug</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сомнение</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>doubt</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>колебание</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>hesitation</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сомневающийся</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>doubtful</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>колеблющийся</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>hesitating</q></cit></sense></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Буквально „двусердие“; см. <xr><ref target="#entry_dy-"/></xr> | %idu%i и <xr><ref target="#entry_zærdæ"/></xr> ‘сердце’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>dödil</w><gloss><q>сомневающийся</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>колеблющийся</q></gloss></mentioned>, , буквально „двусердый“. Такое же образование, но с иным значением, в грузинском: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>orguli</w><gloss><q>вероломный</q></gloss></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ori</w><gloss><q>два</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>guli</w><gloss><q>сердце</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_īwzærdyg"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>48, 90</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Literally “double-heartness”; see <xr><ref target="#entry_dy-"/></xr> | %idu%i and <xr><ref target="#entry_zærdæ"/></xr> ‘heary’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>dödil</w><gloss><q>doubtful</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>hesitating</q></gloss></mentioned>, , literally “two hearted”. The same derivative but with another meaning is found in Georgian: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>orguli</w><gloss><q>faithless</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ori</w><gloss><q>two</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>guli</w><gloss><q>heart</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_īwzærdyg"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>48, 90</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>